      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Author, editor, translator, literary agent in Paris. Columbia
            University B.A. 1899, M.A. 1900.</p>
         <p/>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>Correspondence, manuscripts, notes, documents, clippings, periodicals, and books
            including Bradley's writings while at Columbia University, his poetry and short stories
            about the Kentucky mountains, his translations of various French authors, his writings
            on printing history, art, and health, and his other contributions to periodicals.
            Correspondents include John Kendrick Bangs and William Goddell Frost.</p>
         <p/>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Selected materials cataloged; remainder arranged. This collection is arranged in one
            series: <list type="marked">
                    <item>Series I: William Aspenwall Bradley Papers,
                  1900-1966</item>
                </list>
            </p>
      </arrangement>
